===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*haira-'', from Indo-European ''*kei-, *koi-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[her|hēr]], Old High German [[her|hēr]] (German [[hehr]] ‘august, holy’), Old Norse [[hárr]] ‘grey’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ha:ɹ/

===Adjective===
'''hār'''
# grey-haired, [[old]] and [[grey]], [[venerable]]

